# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LegalEase Frontend Environment Variables (Firebase Configuration)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ─── Backend API URL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local development: http://localhost:3001
# Render deployment: https://your-backend-service.onrender.com
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
# ─── Firebase Authentication & Services ────────────────────────────────────────
# Get these values from your Firebase Console:
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to Project Settings (gear icon)
# 4. Copy values from the "General" tab and "serviceAccounts" tab

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Rename this file to .env
# 2. Fill in all Firebase credentials with your actual project values
# 3. Start the frontend with: npm run dev
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
